|caption=Average recall of items at final test.  Goodmon and Anderson (2011) showed not only that prior retrieval enhances later retrieval of those same words (Rp+ items), but that remembering words ''related'' to practiced words (Rp- items) can suffer as a result of prior retrieval compared to unrelated words (NRp items).  By comparing the recall for Rp- and NRp items, the experiment showed a 13% RIF effect.
